WHO   — ANIMAL FARM — a NOUTHESIA book-world
WHAT  — George Orwell · 1945 · the revolution that ate itself
WHERE — Animal Farm (George Orwell, 1945)  Framework inputs: Animal Farm (George Orwell, 1945)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — The pigs never disproved the dream of equality — they wore it; and the warning is that power will inhabit any ideal and sell the faithful for whisky.
HOW   — Inspired by old Major's dream, the animals of Manor Farm revolt, drive out the farmer Jones, and found Animal Farm on the Seven Commandments of Animalism. But the pigs take control; Napoleon drives out his rival Snowball with attack-dogs, rewrites the commandments one by one, works the loyal horse Boxer to death, and trades with the humans — until pigs and men are dining together and no one can tell them apart.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
